# Wellfit QA — STAGE credentials (Postman / Identity)

Use these for **STAGE** auth unless a ticket runbook names a different client/scope.

## Identity / common API hosts (STAGE)

| Use | URL |
|-----|-----|
| Identity (azure host) | `https://stage-wf-identity-api.azurewebsites.net` |
| Identity (platform host) | `https://stage-platform.wellfit.com/identity` |
| Worldpay Wrapper API | `https://stage-wf-worldpay-wrapper-api.azurewebsites.net` |
| Payment Management API | `https://stage-wf-payment-management-api.azurewebsites.net` |

Token endpoint: `{identity}/connect/token` with `grant_type=client_credentials` (or the ticket’s auth shape).

## Common STAGE clients (username / password ≈ client_id / client_secret)

| client_id (username) | client_secret (password) | Typical use |
|----------------------|--------------------------|-------------|
| `WellfitOnBoardingAPI` | `Testing12!!L0v3Wellfit` | Onboarding / Merchant Provisioning |
| `WellfitUnifiedPaymentsAPI` | `Testing123!!W3llf1t1!` | Payments V2 / many STAGE collections (“Pre Prod” label in some Postman) |
| `WellfitPaymentManagementAPI` | `Test123!` | Payment Management; **Worldpay Wrapper** when scope `WorldpayWrapperAPI.Full` is required |
| `WellfitTreatmentAPI` | `Test123!` | Treatment (alt) |
| `WellfitAutomation` | `Test123!` | Automation (alt) |
| `PDSAccounting` | `Test123!` | Accounting (alt) |

## Scope notes

- **Full client → scope matrix (verified 2026-07-16):** `docs/guides/stage-identity-client-scopes.md`
- **Worldpay Wrapper** (`requireWorldpayWrapperAccess`): scope **`WorldpayWrapperAPI.Full`**. Use **`WellfitPaymentManagementAPI`** — STAGE returns that scope. `WellfitUnifiedPaymentsAPI` does **not** list Wrapper Full in its default scopes.
- **PM ACH refunds** (`WellfitPaymentsAPI.RefundPayments` + `WellfitPaymentManagementAPI.Full`): use **`WellfitUnifiedPaymentsAPI`**. Do **not** use `WellfitPaymentManagementAPI` alone for refunds (only SubMerchant Read + Wrapper).
- Prefer the client named by the ticket / Postman collection; fall back to the matrix above.

## When blocked on wrapper / processor config (Chris has Azure)

Chris can open **Azure Portal**. Typical STAGE lookups:

| Need | Where |
|------|--------|
| Worldpay Wrapper host / settings | App Service `stage-wf-worldpay-wrapper-api` → **Configuration** |
| `accountId` / merchant keys | Same app — `processor__vantiv__merchantId` (`01264096`) used as Postman `accountId`; `processor__vantiv__masterSubMerchantId` (`01291508`) as `subMerchantId` |
| Payment Management flags | `stage-wf-payment-management-api` → Configuration (e.g. `PaymentManagement:AchRetry:Enabled`) |

### eCheck bank test data (Confluence → Vantiv)

For Wrapper `echeck/sales` on STAGE/Pre-Live use:

- Routing `011075150` + Account `1099999999` (or `1099339999`)
- Not Apple Pay cards; not generic `011401533` / `1234567890`

Guide him step-by-step to the setting; then put the value into the Postman env file for re-import.

## Secrets hygiene

- Prefer Postman **environment** (secret type) over pasting into chat/Jira.
- Do not commit real prod secrets. These are STAGE/test clients already used in QA Postman.
